</emphasis>
-. Ocellar setae pair I present, pair III arise outside the triangle (
<figureCitation box="[794,849,274,295]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1707,1729]" captionTargetBox="[196,1400,182,1688]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[196,1401,182,1688]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Biltothrips perakensis sp. n: (1) Head; (2) Pteronota; (3) Antennal segments I − VIII; (4) Abdominal tergites III – VI; (5) Abdominal tergites VI – X; (6) Fore wing; (7) Sternites IV – VII; (8) Meso- and metasterna." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258660/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="142">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
); head without sculpture in ocellar area; tergites IV–VI with setal pair I much smaller than pair II, and arising mesad of CPS (
<figureCitation box="[826,885,303,324]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1707,1729]" captionTargetBox="[196,1400,182,1688]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[196,1401,182,1688]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Biltothrips perakensis sp. n: (1) Head; (2) Pteronota; (3) Antennal segments I − VIII; (4) Abdominal tergites III – VI; (5) Abdominal tergites VI – X; (6) Fore wing; (7) Sternites IV – VII; (8) Meso- and metasterna." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258660/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="142">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
); sternites with microtrichial rows only laterally (
<figureCitation box="[1364,1422,303,324]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1707,1729]" captionTargetBox="[196,1400,182,1688]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[196,1401,182,1688]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Biltothrips perakensis sp. n: (1) Head; (2) Pteronota; (3) Antennal segments I − VIII; (4) Abdominal tergites III – VI; (5) Abdominal tergites VI – X; (6) Fore wing; (7) Sternites IV – VII; (8) Meso- and metasterna." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258660/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="142">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
); fore wing second vein with 3 setae 
